# CompanyScope architecture rules

## Preferred stack
- Frontend: Next.js, TypeScript, Tailwind, shadcn/ui
- Backend API: FastAPI
- Background workers: Celery or Dramatiq
- Database: PostgreSQL
- Cache and queue: Redis
- Object storage: MinIO
- Monitoring: Prometheus, Grafana, Loki

## Architectural direction
Use a modular monorepo with separate app boundaries for:
- web app
- API service
- worker service

Recommended structure:

```text
/apps
  /web
  /api
  /worker
/packages
  /schemas
  /ui
  /config
/docs
```

## Service boundaries
### Web app
Responsible for:
- UI rendering
- client-side interactions
- authenticated user flows
- calling internal API only

### API service
Responsible for:
- Companies House integration
- aggregate company endpoints
- auth and watchlist endpoints
- persistence orchestration
- signal generation requests

### Worker service
Responsible for:
- ingestion jobs
- document fetch jobs
- parser jobs
- refresh scheduling
- reprocessing and repair jobs

## Upstream API usage rules
- Never call Companies House directly from the browser
- Keep Companies House API keys server-side only
- Use caching and background hydration aggressively
- Treat parser extraction as best-effort, not guaranteed

## Data modelling direction
- Store period-based financial facts
- Preserve source provenance for every extracted fact
- Version parser runs and methodology changes
- Do not overwrite raw extraction history destructively
